# **THE CLARITY FRAMEWORK — TYPOGRAPHY SYSTEM v1.0**

*A unified type system engineered specifically for high-signal AI-generated documentation.*

---

# **1. BRAND TYPEFACES**

### **Primary Typeface — “Inter” (Modern, Rational, Universal)**

Use for:
Headings, subheadings, UI labels, metadata, mode-tag labels.

**Weights used:**

* Inter Black — H1
* Inter Bold — H2, H3
* Inter SemiBold — labels, section headers
* Inter Medium — UI scaffolding
* Inter Regular — body text

Why Inter?
Because it reads clean at all sizes, renders consistently across platforms, and reinforces the framework’s purpose: **unambiguous clarity**.

---

### **Secondary Typeface — “Source Serif Pro” (Editorial Depth)**

Use for:
Body text in longform documents, footnotes, annotations, philosophical context.

**Weights used:**

* Regular
* Semibold

Why a serif companion?
It creates cognitive segmentation:
Sans = operational.
Serif = conceptual.

Perfect for your style.

---

### **Accent Typeface — “Space Grotesk” (Signal + Branding)**

Use for:
Mode badges (EXECUTION, INSTRUCTION, COPY-PASTE),
high-impact callouts,
section dividers,
pull quotes.

**Weights:**

* Bold
* Medium

This is the “identity flavor” that separates your framework from generic documentation.

---

# **2. TYPOGRAPHIC HIERARCHY**

### **H1 — Framework Title / Major Section Titles**

Font: *Inter Black*
Size: 44–52px
Tracking: -1%
Case: Title Case
Color: #0A0A0A or #101010

Used for:
“The Clarity Framework v1.0”,
“Intent Signal”.

---

### **H2 — Section Headers**

Font: *Inter Bold*
Size: 28–32px
Tracking: -0.5%
Case: Title Case
Color: #111

Used for:
“Execution Context”,
“Output Classification”.

---

### **H3 — Subsections / Category Blocks**

Font: *Inter Semibold*
Size: 20–22px
Line height: 135%
Color: #1A1A1A

Used for:
“What It Is”,
“What It Is Not”,
“Use Cases”, etc.

---

### **Body Text (Primary)**

Font: *Source Serif Pro Regular*
Size: 16–18px
Line height: 150–165%
Color: #222

Used for:
Explanations, paragraphs, guidance.

---

### **Body Text (Secondary / Notes)**

Font: *Inter Regular*
Size: 14–15px
Color: #444

Used for:
Implementation notes, labels, metadata.

---

# **3. SPECIALIZED ELEMENTS**

### **Intent Labels (Mode Tags)**

Font: *Space Grotesk Bold*
Size: 12–14px
Letter spacing: 3–6px
Case: UPPERCASE
Color coding:

* **EXECUTION MODE** → #0070F3 (blue)
* **INSTRUCTION MODE** → #A855F7 (violet)
* **COPY-PASTE SAFE** → #10B981 (green)
* **ARCHIVAL** → #F59E0B (amber)
* **EXPERIMENTAL** → #EF4444 (red)

Badge style:
Rounded corners (4–6px), 1px stroke #DDD, 4px padding.

---

### **Pull Quotes / Callouts**

Font: *Space Grotesk Medium*
Size: 20–24px
Line height: 140%
Color: #0E0E0E

Used when calling out principles, e.g.:
“Clarity is not optional—it’s the infrastructure of trust.”

---

### **Numbered Framework Steps**

Font: *Inter Bold*
Size: 18px
Color: #000
Spacing: 8px vertical

Style example:

1. Intent signal
2. Execution context
3. Output classification

---

# **4. SPACING SYSTEM**

Use a vertical rhythm based on **8px increments**:

* Small spacing: 8px
* Standard spacing: 16px
* Block spacing: 24px
* Section spacing: 48px
* Page breaks / macro sections: 72px

This creates psychological “breathing room” for fast scanning.

---

# **5. COLOR PALETTE**

### **Neutral Core**

* Carbon Black: #0A0A0A
* Slate Grey: #2A2A2A
* Soft Grey: #E5E5E5
* Paper White: #FAFAFA

### **Accent System (Aligned to Mode Tags)**

* Blueprint Blue: #0070F3
* Signal Violet: #A855F7
* Clarity Green: #10B981
* Archive Amber: #F59E0B
* Experimental Red: #EF4444

---

# **6. BRAND COMPONENTS**

### **Section Dividers**

1px line, #E1E1E1, full bleed.
Spacing: 32px above, 32px below.

---

### **Meta Labels (for transparency)**

Font: *Inter Medium*
Size: 11–12px
Color: #666
Uppercase, spaced letters
Used for:

* “Generated by AI”
* “Intent: Instruction”
* “Execution Context Included”

---

# **7. PORTABLE STYLE BLOCK (COPY-PASTE FOR OTHER LLMS)**

*(No code formatting used — safe text that preserves system integrity)*

**Typography System — The Clarity Framework
Primary: Inter (Black/Bold/Semibold/Regular)
Secondary: Source Serif Pro (Regular/Semibold)
Accent: Space Grotesk (Medium/Bold)**

Title hierarchy:
H1: Inter Black, 44–52px
H2: Inter Bold, 28–32px
H3: Inter Semibold, 20–22px

Body:
Source Serif Pro Regular, 16–18px, 150–165% line height
Notes: Inter Regular, 14–15px

Mode Tags (uppercase):
Space Grotesk Bold, 12–14px, tracking 3–6px
Colors:
EXECUTION #0070F3
INSTRUCTION #A855F7
COPY-PASTE #10B981
ARCHIVAL #F59E0B
EXPERIMENTAL #EF4444

Spacing Rhythm: 8px grid
Dividers: 1px #E1E1E1, 32px spacing

Use this system to format and brand all Clarity Framework documentation across PDFs, websites, and LLM outputs.

---


